A couple has been arrested in Gauteng for violating lockdown regulations JOHANNESBURG - A couple has been arrested in Gauteng for violating lockdown regulations. During a routine roadblock on the N12, police asked the man to open his boot. There they discovered his girlfriend who he was attempting to smuggle out of the province, to Mpumalanga. READ: Foreign-owned spaza shops on Cape Flats feel threatened He was travelling without a permit and she was arrested for consenting to be smuggled. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.